review_blob: 2004 Bottle.  From the fantastic aroma and lovely thick head, to the jet black pour, this beer is a delight to the senses.  Until you drink it; then it delights again.  The sweet oats; the round mouthfeel; and the bright hoppy finish make this beer one of my favourites!
Lovely strong aroma, with an excellent palate.  The finish warms the body on the coldest night.  It's too bad it's such a strong beer; I'd love to drink it more!
Very thin mouthfeel with a surprising chocolate flavor.  Not really worth the money or the time.  Drink something else.
